houseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rangers, Archery Mastery 3, and the Crown of Damage Deal</span><hr size=1> You want to make this a fair discussion?  Then you need to even the playing field a little.<br><br>1- If any part of a mob is touching a wall, you cannot hit it in melee combat.<br><br>2- You can only double backstab every 72 min.<br><br>3- You must spend 36 AA points before you are allowed to backstab.<br><br>4- If a mob is moving or rooted, you can only do 1/2 damage to it.<br><br>Once these conditions are met, then you have all the right in the world to complain.<br><br>That being said, I believe that this post is totally absurd.  Archery is at best broken, and completely situational.  The damage logs were taken on an extremely low AC mob, and one that archery can be used against effectively.  When we are shooting our bows and the mob is either too high on the z axis or either a part of their body is touching an obstruction, then the arrows disappear into nowhere.  There are countless disciplines I have wasted on a drake or the like in ToV that I believe I have a chance at hitting and then get pushed into a wall and poof, grats wasted disc.  Also, being that archery is not on an auto attack system, any lag results in several lost shots, meaning every raid will not come up to par with the numbers posted here.<br><br>Against the 1st Rhag in Ssra (not THAT difficult a mob at all) even with trueshot, I was getting worthless damage from archery.  30 sec into my disc I switched to plain melee.  Just wasn't worth it.  With the absurd AC of most mobs today, you will never see dps like that posted in the logs.<br><br>Please don't make an EXTREMELY situational disc or viable archery situation look like the norm for everyday play.  In certain areas, yes, archery is now a viable way to do damage (might want to add that rangers have been asking for archery as a viable means of combat since day 1- it's our symbol for God's sake), however, in most, it's not.<br><br>Rangers have been the whipping boy and butt of jokes for a long time in EQ.  Finally, when we get a small bone thrown to us after extreme work and dedication by us, the ranger community, certain rogues like yourself try to hold us back.  Remember back to before rogues were even played by anyone because they were totally useless and remember how happy the rogue community was when they were given a place in eq that &quot;fit&quot;.  You didn't see an outcry by the ranger community to nerf them did you?  Otherwise, you might still be without backstab, etc.<br><br>Please focus on rogue balance issues, not rangers.  Archery is NOT a breaking point of the masters of melee damage, the rogue. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/electronic/Everquestakirotag/JAROUTTAG.html"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uevertorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evertorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 3:41:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rangers, Archery Mastery 3, and the Crown of Damage Deal</span><hr size=1> Grats for Rangers.<br>I'm curious, to do the 321dps what does that cost per hour?  100pp? 500pp?<br><br>Rogues are still the king of melee, because our melee isn't situational, where as archery is.<br><br>Grats to Rangers again though, hopefully now there will be some weapon upgrades for you guys and gals.<br><br>Side note: I read a few posts on the Rangerglade, saddens me that immediately there is mention of rogues crying nerf at the nerfhouse.  You won't see rogues crying nerf, at least the ones that know how to play the game/class.  <br>Oh well, can't win every battle. <p><center><font size=1><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7500>Evertorrn DarkHeart</a> - Level 58 Blackguard <BR>    <I>“My Word is my Honor, My Honor is my Life..”</I><BR>    <I>“My blood for your blood..”</I><BR><I>“Strength and Honor..”</I><BR>"<b>We</b> will be <b>perfect</b> in <b>every aspect</b> of the <b>game</b>. You drop a pass...you run a mile, you miss a blocking assignment...you run a mile, you fumble the football...and I will break my foot off in your John Brown hind parts and <u>then</u> you will run a mile. <b>Perfection</b>...it's what I want."</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujareckthundershot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jareck Thundershot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 3:42:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rangers, Archery Mastery 3, and the Crown of Damage Deal</span><hr size=1> PS- Thanks to the other rogues who replied before I got my reply in.  None were up when I started my last post =)<br><br><br><i>Sig nerfed per rules.  Signatures allowed once per thread.  Please read our <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessage?topicID=21681.topic>Forum Rules</a> at the top of the Main Lounge.  Thankyou.  --Gyorg</i><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gyorg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/18/02 6:09:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valig