uelist (3-4 backstabs in the 900+ range, doubled, so like 8k, and another 5-7k in normal melee)...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>And all that requires is four crit backstabs during a duelist?  No, that's not unreasonable...<br><br>Your numbers are too high by at least a factor a four, no rogue comes anywhere near 1kdps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udober9910.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dober9910</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 4:29:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rangers, Archery Mastery 3, and the Crown of Damage Deal</span><hr size=1> &quot;I'm curious, to do the 321dps what does that cost per hour? 100pp? 500pp?&quot;<br><br>Actually costs nothing using endless quiver.  There are ways around part of the archery problems such as when a mob gets in a wall, move around and stand in the same wall (if space permits).  Usually the non-moving part is not a concern.  Once the MT has agro, the mob stays unless someone is doing their job wrong (such as over-nuking and ping-ponging a mob).  <br><br>Not gonna say that over the long run a Ranger is going to outdamage a Rogue.  A Ranger is part melee and part buffs.  I haven't seen many melees that turn down attack buffs to help increase their damage.  Being top damage do'er and also buffing others to do more damage would be the best of both worlds.  Not gonna happen, but in the mean time we will still do great damage.<br><br>Dober<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulothanebonhart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lothan Ebonhart</A></