Notice the almost immediate &quot;grats rangers&quot;. Almost everyone here already knows this stuff, and yet they reply with positive posts to try and prevent this from becoming like one of those other threads.<br><br>Oh and this guy isn't even a rogue. Remember that although the safehouse is for rogues, they can't seem to keep other people from coming here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Hmm one last opinion, I think both archery and backstab are situational, but everyone knows how powerful backstab is and so &quot;tries&quot; to accomodate the rogues. Although I don't speak with experience of high end mob raiding, I think it is possible the same thing will happen with archery. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usilouettesas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silouette SaS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 5:15:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rangers, Archery Mastery 3, and the Crown of Damage Deal</span><hr size=1> Raise your hands if you know a 60 Rogue with his epic...*watches all the hands fly up*<br><br>Now Raise you hands if you know a 60 ranger...<br>With his Epic...<br>With 36 AA points...<br>With a Fleeting Quiver...<br>That has a Primal Bow...<br>With a rare drop arrow<br>*watches the hands that were up for the first part drop as the options get more precise*<br><br>Now with that said, if a ranger is able to get this damage potential as easy as a Rogue gets his Epic/60...THEN i can see the need for bringing this up. But the fact remains that it is considerably harder for a ranger to meet all the conditions and THEN some (LoS, lag and what not) to even situationally out damage a rogue. <br><br>Rogues still wear the crown of &quot;Melee damage King&quot;...or however the troll...errrr..Originator of this post put it<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umortok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mortok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 5:22:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Most of the rangers got a little peeved when that ranger vs. rogue thread came out so I am sure you guys can give us a little slack to the few negative comments said on the Ranger Glade.  Overall most rangers know who is the king of melee... its the rogue.  Sure we can do awesome damage ever 72 minutes but like it has been said a million times before it is very situational whereas backstab is fairly reliable.  <br><br>Thank you for all the nice comments.  Its nice to be able to use archery now and then and know it is effective   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unimmbull.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimmbull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 6:01:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</s