is that other mellee classes need some AXP route to increase damage output by an appreciable amount.  Chaotic Stab is a decent increase, although with good agro control in high end encounters it's not unreasonable to see the back of a mob more than 95% or more of the time, making chaotic stab a fairly minor increase in damage.  Ambidexterity is by far a better upgrade for monks than for rogues, who rely much more on the primary hand for damage output.  The Archetype skills were supposed to be a way to customize your character, however there are realistically only 2 or 3 viable paths through AXP for a smart rogue, some would say less.  <br><br>Run 3 -&gt; Regen 3 -&gt; Crits1(if that even) then Stability or Durability -&gt; Chaotic Stab -&gt; Ambidexterity or Escape -&gt; back to archetype skills.  <br><br>The opportunity for advancement is actually quite narrow, skills like acrobatics, purge poison (which is completely useless because it's only possible use, curing poison dot aes, is nullified by the 72 minuete re use timer.  Should be made either poison immunity or have it's re use timer reduced a GREAT deal), poison mastery (Poison = near zero viability in it's current implementation, needs to be made stackable, applyable while standing) aren't worth getting for most rogues, I dare say any.  VI, as they have many times before, overcompensated for previously making rogues masters of mellee damage by toning down their luclin abilities to useless or near useless.  <br><br>And in comparing trueshot to duelist, trueshot is by far the more superior discipline.  Trueshot lasts 2 min?, Duelist 15 seconds, both will approximately double? damage output.  The shorter refresh time on duelist is of little consequence when considering the amount of boss mob encounters that last for more than 29 minuetes.  Using Duelist in a 5 minuete encounter will up damage output by a paltry 5%, using trueshot in a 5 minuete encounter will up damage output by 40% (assuming 100% bow shots).  <br><br>The only problem I have with ranger bow damage with AM3 and endless quiver is pvp =p.  Being able to 1 or 2 round a caster without regard to mellee distance is unbalancing.  The only thing that gives casters a chance against mellees in pvp is the fact that mellees require close range to be able to deal damage.  Even counting in the line of sight factor, bow damage is still unbalancing.  Bow damage needs to be nerfed to 2/3 in pvp as nuke damage is.  Although it's not like pvp servers ever get any attention as it is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 7:26:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22878.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rangers, Archery Mastery 3, and the Crown of Damage Deal</span><hr size=1> An interesting note about walls eating arrows from the ranger boards.<br><br>Generally speaking your arrows will not be eaten if you are touching the same wall as the mob and the wall is parellel to the invisible line between you and the mob.  This is because no collision detection is done with zone walls that lie parellel to the line of sight because they cannot interesect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukitai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kitai</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.netdesign.net/~kitae/little-cat.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registere